00:00:15.028 --> 00:00:18.500
Masikat or Masi lives in Recto, Avenida.

00:00:18.857 --> 00:00:22.218
In the cluster of houses
in front of the provincial bus station

00:00:22.267 --> 00:00:23.915
at the back of Manila City Jail.

00:00:24.412 --> 00:00:28.340
In a community that
depends on pedicab driving,

00:00:28.479 --> 00:00:31.279
if not stealing things
or selling drugs.

00:00:31.487 --> 00:00:34.831
Most of the women
have stalls around Divisoria

00:00:34.906 --> 00:00:39.011
if not doing the classic livelihood
of doing laundry.

00:00:39.676 --> 00:00:41.308
Masi is 16 years old

00:00:41.539 --> 00:00:46.637
and his dream is to leave
the housefly-infested town.

00:00:46.802 --> 00:00:49.841
His tidy appearance is a stark contrast
the griminess of Recto,

00:00:49.903 --> 00:00:52.379
unblemished with no scars or scratches.

00:00:52.676 --> 00:00:56.754
If he was left in the affluent part of town,
and was dressed up a bit,

00:00:56.923 --> 00:00:59.832
he could pass off as a resident
of that neighborhood.

00:00:59.997 --> 00:01:03.287
He’s not that smart,
but his dream is big enough.

00:01:03.548 --> 00:01:07.348
Intelligence shouldn’t be measured
in the way one speaks

00:01:07.598 --> 00:01:13.461
or in one’s broken English,
but in the way one can explain things

00:01:13.821 --> 00:01:16.576
which could be learnt
at school or outside.

00:01:16.865 --> 00:01:21.569
But the things that Masi lacks
is what makes him interesting.

00:01:21.819 --> 00:01:23.933
He has a good grasp on education

00:01:24.106 --> 00:01:26.523
and strongly believes
it’ll give him a better life.

00:01:26.812 --> 00:01:30.158
He usually hangs out at Dan’s place,
also known as Daddy.

00:01:30.301 --> 00:01:33.113
Dan is one of those people
who are well-off.

00:01:33.388 --> 00:01:39.390
Masi often stays at other places,
especially since he lives in a cramped house.

00:01:39.579 --> 00:01:41.578
Masi only knows that Dan’s a model.

00:01:41.641 --> 00:01:43.982
Dan leaves at night
with an extremely powdered face

00:01:44.037 --> 00:01:46.209
and comes back still smelling good
in the morning.

00:01:47.655 --> 00:01:50.670
Masi takes care of Dan’s house.

00:01:50.755 --> 00:01:56.635
From cleaning his shoes
to folding his shiny underwear.

00:01:56.736 --> 00:02:00.479
Masi could almost be Dan's partner,

00:02:00.512 --> 00:02:02.263
although he calls him Daddy.

00:02:02.635 --> 00:02:07.767
In fact, they’re already like a couple
since they sleep together.

00:02:07.838 --> 00:02:11.541
In exchange, Dan pays for his tuition.

00:02:11.700 --> 00:02:13.851
But Masi doesn’t feel like a prostitute

00:02:13.887 --> 00:02:16.209
especially since he respects
and loves Dan so much.

00:02:16.577 --> 00:02:20.153
Until one day, Masi came down
with an intense fever.

00:02:20.739 --> 00:02:22.641
His mother even had to bring him
to the hospital,

00:02:22.695 --> 00:02:25.446
and that’s where he found out
that he was sick.

00:02:25.802 --> 00:02:27.521
He was HIV positive.

00:02:28.056 --> 00:02:29.474
That’s the description.

00:02:29.762 --> 00:02:31.327
For the monologue,

00:02:31.452 --> 00:02:32.936
I set it at dusk

00:02:32.980 --> 00:02:35.686
inside a broken pedicab
at the sidewalk.

00:02:36.244 --> 00:02:38.880
Masi's face to face
with his bestfriend, Lily.

00:02:39.018 --> 00:02:42.551
Holding the paper
that San Lazaro Hospital gave him.

00:02:42.748 --> 00:02:45.615
Lily is crying nonstop
while Masi is talking.

00:02:46.869 --> 00:02:47.510
Masi.

00:02:48.395 --> 00:02:50.749
Masi: “You keep on crying, honey.
It’s so annoying.”

00:02:50.794 --> 00:02:51.751
“Stop it, already.”

00:02:51.829 --> 00:02:52.484
“Why?”

00:02:52.532 --> 00:02:53.625
He slaps her cheek.

00:02:54.181 --> 00:02:55.467
"I'm still okay."

00:02:55.835 --> 00:02:57.248
“You’re too judgmental.”

00:02:57.327 --> 00:03:00.578
“The doctor said
that the Human-Inum—"

00:03:00.657 --> 00:03:02.408
"Fuck, just read it. It’s all there.”

00:03:04.633 --> 00:03:06.098
“I just have to take some meds.”

00:03:06.190 --> 00:03:07.471
“I won’t die.”

00:03:07.589 --> 00:03:09.102
“He said it’s just like diabetes.”

00:03:09.142 --> 00:03:11.079
“In fact, my mother’s worries faded.”

00:03:11.157 --> 00:03:13.793
“Because even grandma
has diabetes and she’s still alive.”

00:03:13.899 --> 00:03:17.214
“My god, honey!
Think of how many meds I’ll take!”

00:03:17.426 --> 00:03:19.309
“Aren’t the rich like that?”

00:03:19.599 --> 00:03:22.614
“But dear, the meds have a side effect.”

00:03:22.739 --> 00:03:26.249
“It’s like you’re dreaming
or you’re seeing things.”

00:03:26.342 --> 00:03:29.806
“Maybe Recto might look better
and less ugly with this.”

00:03:29.861 --> 00:03:32.640
“Maybe this Human inum-inum
could disappear.”

00:03:32.770 --> 00:03:35.412
“Maybe I could still go to Daddy.”

00:03:35.826 --> 00:03:40.200
“That’s all I see when there’s—
Fuck! It’s so hard to pronounce.”

00:03:40.287 --> 00:03:41.653
There are cracks in his voice.

00:03:41.928 --> 00:03:43.522
Lily: “Stop crying, dear.”

00:03:44.219 --> 00:03:45.798
“I’ll still do your makeup.”

00:03:45.857 --> 00:03:47.087
“We’ll still go to school together.”

00:03:47.165 --> 00:03:48.748
”We’ll still be on fleek together.”

00:03:48.839 --> 00:03:51.327
Masi: “I won’t die yet, right?”

00:03:51.395 --> 00:03:53.149
“Come on! Give me the paper, hon.”

00:04:00.147 --> 00:04:01.938
It’s like a short story.

